# $env:HTTPS="true"; npm start

# Explanation:
# Create React App provides a convenient environment variable, `HTTPS`, which when set to `true`, instructs the underlying webpack-dev-server to serve the application over HTTPS. It automatically generates and uses a self-signed certificate, which your browser might initially warn you about, but you can proceed past the warning for `localhost`.
